GLOBAL DASHBOARD RULES — 7 FJELL BRYGGERI BI SUITE
Schema: "7fsalg"




These rules apply across all dashboards, all marts, and all SQL.
No exceptions without explicit documentation.




--------------------------------------------------
TIME GRAIN
--------------------------------------------------




Base grain:         Monthly
                    All foundation marts built at monthly level
                    Quarterly and yearly are aggregations on top
                    Never build a foundation mart at a higher grain
                    than monthly




ISO week:           Available in date_dim for event-level analysis
                    Used in Dashboard 2 only for structural event context
                    (covid_phase, is_17_mai, vmp_juleol_launch,
                    dagligvare_assortment_cycle)
                    Never used as base grain for foundation marts




LY comparison:      Same month prior year
                    e.g. January 2026 vs January 2025
                    Never compare calendar date vs calendar date
                    Reason: brewery operates Mon–Fri — same date in
                    different years falls on different weekdays




--------------------------------------------------
TIME WINDOW DEFINITIONS
--------------------------------------------------




Calendar year:      Jan 1 to Dec 31 — fixed, closed once year ends
                    Used for historical year comparisons




YTD:                Jan 1 of current year to current date
                    Always compared against same period LY
                    Filter in Metabase: year = current year (relative)




Rolling 12 months:  Pre-calculated in PostgreSQL analytical marts
                    Never calculated via Metabase date filters




--------------------------------------------------
ANALYTICAL LOGIC — POSTGRESQL ONLY
--------------------------------------------------




All YoY, rolling window, and index calculations live in PostgreSQL marts.
Never implement analytical logic in Metabase UI.


Specifically prohibited in Metabase:
- YoY via Offset()           — produces NULL when date filters are applied
- Rolling windows via sums   — cannot reach outside a filtered dataset
- Index calculations         — must be consistent across all dashboards




Source for all analytical metrics:
- YoY and rolling:   analytical time-series marts
- Index values:      index normalisation marts
- Growth cohorts:    mart_sales_growth_decomposition_monthly




Refer to the master view registry for current mart assignments per dashboard.




--------------------------------------------------
PRIMARY MEASURE
--------------------------------------------------




Volume:             analysis_volume_litres — sole authoritative measure
                    All dashboards are volume-based




Revenue:            Excluded from all dashboards by default
                    Reason: grossist invoicing uses lump sums without
                    SKU breakdown — contaminates product and customer
                    revenue figures across the dataset


                    Permitted only where explicitly documented:
                    Dashboard 4 — direct customers only
                    mart_sales_monthly_yoy — total business level, caveat applies


Estimated contribution: SUM(estimated_contribution_nok) — sole authoritative
                        contribution measure
                        Source: mart_pricing_margin_monthly
                        Grain is sku × customer × channel × month
                        Always aggregate with SUM in Metabase
                        Never use AVG — produces per-customer average,
                        not a portfolio or channel total
                        NULL for all periods prior to 2026
                        (no pricing data exists before this date)




--------------------------------------------------
NULL & ZERO HANDLING
--------------------------------------------------




Zero months:        A month with no sales = zero, not NULL
                    Zero-filling only within active lifespan of entity
                    Active lifespan = first sale → last sale
                    No zero-filling before first sale or after last sale
                    No zero-filling for combinations that never traded
                    Requires a date spine in relevant marts




Application:
                    Foundation marts          — no zero-filling
                    Dashboard 3 product marts — within SKU lifespan
                    Dashboard 4 customer marts — within customer lifespan
                    Dashboards 1 and 5        — no zero-filling needed




NULLs in dims:      Allowed where documented in schema
                    Never coerce to zero or placeholder value




--------------------------------------------------
NEGATIVE ROWS
--------------------------------------------------




First-class data — never silently stripped.
Represent real commercial events: returns, credits, destructions.


Board views:        Show netted totals (positive + negative combined)
Drill-down views:   May surface negatives explicitly for anomaly analysis


Marts must never exclude negatives without explicit documentation
and a clear analytical reason.




--------------------------------------------------
DISPLAY & LABELLING STANDARDS
--------------------------------------------------




Machine names:      Never surface raw column names in Metabase
                    All marts must use human-readable aliases




Label standard:     INITCAP(REPLACE(column, '_', ' '))
                    e.g. glass_bottle_screwcap → Glass Bottle Screwcap
                         direktsalg_horeca     → Direktsalg Horeca




SKU display:        clean_product_name || ' – '
                    || INITCAP(REPLACE(unit_type, '_', ' '))
                    || ' (' || sku || ')'
                    e.g. Fløien IPA – Glass Bottle (10001)




Norwegian chars:    Preserve ø, æ, å in all display names and labels




--------------------------------------------------
GENERAL RULES
--------------------------------------------------




- Never build a mart without a defined dashboard home
- Never introduce business logic in a mart without documenting it
- All marts derived from sales_fact_core — never from staging or raw
- All table references qualified: "7fsalg".table_name
- Mart naming convention: mart_[subject]_[grain]_[modifier]
- date_dim always joined on invoice_date = date_key
  Never join on derived date parts (year, month, iso_week)
- date_dim does NOT have a quarter column
  Always derive as: EXTRACT(QUARTER FROM date_column)::integer
- All business logic lives in PostgreSQL — not in Metabase UI
  No custom columns, patches, or workarounds in Metabase
